properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first American space station on May 14, 1973, at Cape Canaveral, Florida, U.S.A., by Charles “Pete” Conrad, Joseph Kerwin and Paul Weitz with Skylab space station; cancellation stamp dated May 14, 1984 in Cape Canaveral; includes information on reverse.
